# Project: [CLI TOOL NAME]

## Overview
[Brief description: what this CLI does, target users, primary commands]

## Engineering Standards

**Before writing any Go code**, always read:
```
.claude/skills/golang-skills/SKILL.md
```
Then load: `cli/SKILL.md`, `configuration/SKILL.md`, `packages/cobra-viper/SKILL.md`

## CLI Structure

```
cmd/
└── [toolname]/
    └── main.go          ← thin entrypoint

internal/
├── cli/
│   ├── root.go          ← root cobra command
│   ├── [command].go     ← subcommands
│   └── output.go        ← formatters (table/json/yaml)
├── client/              ← API client(s)
├── config/              ← config types + loader
└── [domain]/            ← business logic
```

## Tech Stack

| Concern | Package | Skill |
|---|---|---|
| CLI framework | `spf13/cobra` + `viper` | `packages/cobra-viper/SKILL.md` |
| Config | `spf13/viper` | `configuration/SKILL.md` |
| HTTP client | `net/http` | `packages/http-std/SKILL.md` |
| Logging | `log/slog` | `packages/slog/SKILL.md` |
| Output | `text/tabwriter` + custom | `cli/SKILL.md` |

## CLI Conventions

- `SilenceUsage: true` — usage shown only on flag errors
- `SilenceErrors: true` — error printing controlled by `main.go`
- All data to `stdout`, all errors/logs to `stderr`
- `--output` flag on all commands: `table` (default) | `json` | `yaml`
- `--dry-run` on all mutating commands
- Exit codes: `0` success, `1` error, `2` usage error, `3` timeout, `4` not found

## Hard Constraints

1. Context with timeout on all network operations
2. All errors returned (never panicked) except programmer errors in `main`
3. `--output json` mode always produces valid parseable JSON to `stdout`
4. Config loaded via viper (env vars override file, flags override env)
5. Shell completion via `completion` subcommand (bash/zsh/fish/powershell)

## Config File

Default location: `~/.config/[toolname]/config.yaml`, then `./config.yaml`
Env prefix: `TOOLNAME_`

## Quality Gates

```bash
make ci   # tidy + vet + lint + test
go test -race -count=1 ./...
```
